# Project Overview

This project is a decision-support map web application that reduces choice overload when selecting restaurants.

Core concept:
Users should be able to decide where to eat within 5 seconds.

Primary goals:
- Reduce search friction
- Remove noisy search results
- Present ONE strong recommendation instead of many options

Target users:
- Busy workers
- Students
- Travelers
- Indecisive users

Core features:
- Genre-filtered map display
- 5-second food diagnosis (3 questions)
- Top1 recommendation logic
- Optional exploration slider

Priority:
P0 stability > P1 UX > P2 optimization

The AI must prioritize shipping working features over architectural perfection.
